{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "nc-collection-v1-001",
    "name": "NutritionCoach API",
    "description": "# NutritionCoach API Test Suite\n\nCovers all REST endpoints exposed by the Spring Boot backend.\n\n**How to use:**\n1. Import `NutritionCoach.postman_environment.json` first.\n2. Select the `NutritionCoach - Local` environment in the top-right dropdown.\n3. Make sure the Spring Boot server is running on port 8080.\n4. Run the full collection via *Collection Runner* or hit requests individually.\n\n**Maintenance rule (see copilot-instructions.md):**\nEvery time a new endpoint is added or an existing one changes its request/response\nshape, this collection AND the environment must be updated in the same PR/commit.\n\n**MERN analogy:**\nThis is the equivalent of a `.rest` file or `supertest` integration tests in a\nNext.js / Express project — but usable without writing code.\n\n**Book ref: Chapter 27 — Evaluations Overview**\nEvals start with basic I/O contract tests (does the endpoint return the right shape?)\nbefore moving on to LLM-output quality evaluation.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "01 - Health & Infra",
      "description": "Liveness probes and infrastructure checks. Run these first to confirm the server is up before executing any AI requests.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /api/health (app liveness)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/health",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "health"]
            },
            "description": "Custom liveness probe built in ChatController.\n\nMERN analogy: `router.get('/health', (req, res) => res.json({ status: 'ok' }))`\n\nExpected: 200 { \"status\": \"ok\" }"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', () => {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Body has status: ok', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('ok');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/health",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "health"]
                }
              },
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
              "body": "{\n    \"status\": \"ok\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
